  "prompt": "Does the TV show Gotham share the same universe with Arrow and The Flash?",
  "response": "No, the TV show \"Gotham\" does not share the same universe as \"Arrow\" and \"The Flash.\" \"Gotham\" is set in its own distinct universe that focuses on the origin stories of various characters from the Batman mythos, particularly Commissioner Jim Gordon and the early days of Gotham City. \n\nOn the other hand, \"Arrow\" and \"The Flash\" are part of what is known as the Arrowverse, which is a shared universe that includes multiple DC Comics-based TV series, such as \"Supergirl,\" \"Legends of Tomorrow,\" and others. While both \"Gotham\" and the Arrowverse series feature characters from DC Comics, they do not cross over or share storylines.",
